Why you want a Nighttime Cleaning Routine ↓ 

Over the years I’ve had a lot of routines… and over the years, life has happened, and lots have changed, fallen away, new ones popped up, etc. However the one routine that has stuck around has been my night time routine.

My nighttime routine varies. It could be a bit more extravagant where I tidy several rooms why my family sleeps, or it could be a bare bones tidy, where only the kitchen & living room get a general clean - and everything in between…

But 95% of the time, we do some type of nightly clean. Some nights I have loads of energy (gotta love insomnia 🫠) and others I can’t keep my eyes open. But I almost always can muster up enough energy and a few minutes of time to clean my dishes, wipe off the counter & pick up whatever randomness is cluttering the main living spaces. 

And it pays to do this at night, because when you don’t… you will be greeted with a mess as soon as you wake up, which will not only add something to your long todo list before you can even get started with your day, but it also creates chaos in your mind in the first moments of the day. It also deters you from wanting to get into the kitchen to make a breakfast to start off the day, or make your morning coffee in peace. And for me, if I spend the first moments of my day cleaning up the kitchen, I have to push off other things from my immediate todo list & it just pushes me further from a peaceful day. 

In the mornings I try to create a calm space for our kids & my husband, because I know it will set their day up for success & keep their mind feeling positive. And I can do that for myself each morning too… but I have to start the night before, with my nighttime cleaning routine

HERE is how we did this bathroom renovation in budget & under a week…

We have referred to this bathroom as our Pepto Bismol Pink bathroom ever since moving in… but we finally took a little under a week & gave it a total makeover, without pulling out the shower, vanity or floors! 

Instead, we started of course with the pink walls, and painted them @benjaminmoore Alabaster… it’s a beautiful, off white color that is the perfect back drop to any bathroom. It’s bright & airy, but still has a warmth to it.

Next we painted the wall behind the sinks with @vasari_plaster_paint Limewash in the color Granite & let the color, texture & dimension add a ton of depth & focus into the space. We swapped out the builder grade mirror for two soft rectangular ones above each sink, added a modern light fixture from @wayfair and immediately you have a totally different bathroom. But we didn’t stop there…

One of my biggest tips for elevating a bathroom, is to swap out the faucets - so we did just that & changed out the outdated faucets, for some affordable, modern faucets we got on Amazon {linked in my LTK} & the other change we made to the existing vanity… was painting the cabinets with @beyondpaintdiy in the color Pebble. I love their paint because it is the easiest way to transform furniture or cabinets, without having to sand or strip anything! We also updated the cabinets/drawers with some cabinet pulls from @amazonhome - And just like that, you have a neutral backdrop & updated vanity area!

Next we moved to the back wall of the bathroom & added a horizontal board & batten wall from some simple wood pieces we got from @homedepot & painted it with @sherwinwilliams Rosemary… a beautiful soft, olive green color! We also added some DIY functional chunky wood shelves (shown in my YouTube video} above the toilet. This added storage, as well as warmth to the space.

After that, we were left with a bathroom that is unrecognizable, & all that was left to do is add the details. Like… painting the rim of the medicine cabinet, adding matte black towel hooks, a rug & stone bath mat & a little decor! To watch the FULL transformation, check out the video on This Crazy Life on YouTube!!

DIY RUSTIC ORNAMENTS are sooo simple to make! ↓ 

Christmas will be here before we know it!! 🎄 So last week I made a few DIYs & here’s how I made my DIY Rustic Ornaments!

*️⃣ You’ll need : 
• several ornaments (in varying sizes)
• acrylic paint (multiple colors, and two shades of each color - ex. Light grey/dark grey, light brown/cream, etc)
• cocoa powder
• baking soda
• a plastic grocery bag
• paint brushes
• spray paint 
• ribbon

1️⃣ Grab several different sized ornaments & remove the tops {you can find them at @dollartree @walmart or even your local thrift store… or use old ones you already have!}

2️⃣ Paint a base coat on your ornaments, choosing the darker tone as the base {if the ornaments are bright colors that don’t match what color you’ll be painting them, I recommend first giving them a coat of spray paint in a neutral color OR painting an additional layer of base paint}

3️⃣ Once they’re {mostly} dry, tear up your plastic bag into small sections, scrunch it up & dab the lighter tone paint all over the ornament, until you like the color variation

4️⃣ Immediately dip your painted ornament into the coordinating powder {cocoa powder for dark & baking soda for the light ones} then gently dry brush off the excess

5️⃣ Let them dry completely & meanwhile, spray paint the ornament tops with your desired color {I opted for gold}

6️⃣ Place the painted tops back on the ornaments & tie a ribbon around the top! {optional… you can seal these with a clear spray paint top coat if desired} 

These are so cute & customizable! You can style them in a bowl or hang them on your tree! 🎄

Every day is different, we have different things on my todo list, varying responsibilities, even our mood isn’t the same from one day to the next. Basically, I’m saying that there is a lot of inconsistency in our days. But for years, I’ve found one single thing that impacts my day more than anything else…

And it might sound small, or silly, or even like an exaggeration 🙃 but it never fails… when my life is feeling chaotic and overwhelming day after day, those are the times when I let this routine slip.

And that simple 2 minute routine is simply… Make your bed every morning… that’s what the experts say 🤗 There are so many studies on this topic and when I started consistently making my bed every single morning, many years ago… I noticed a huge difference! I felt instantly more motivated, I felt accomplished right away, I gained momentum to stay productive in those few minutes - the benefits are all there! 

So I challenge you to make this a goal for the week (if you’re not already doing it) and let me know in one week, if you noticed a difference in your days!? I bet you will! 

And if you’re already part of the “make your bed club” - what is your biggest benefit that you notice from it?

How do you handle kitchen mess?! It’s always a reoccurring thing… but you can… 🙃
1️⃣ clean as you go (this always sounds like the most optimal option, but not always attainable to me, depending on the day) 
2️⃣ clean after each meal (or multiple times a day)
3️⃣ clean once a day (in the morning or night)
4️⃣ no rhyme or reason (just whenever you get to it)

For me, it works best to lightly tidy after each meal, or a few times a day… and then in the evening, after or right before the kids go to bed, I like to go in and do a nightly shut down of our kitchen. During this night time cleaning routine, I wash all the dishes, load up and start the dish washer, clear off & wipe down the counter and call it good! If I’m feeling extra motivated, I’ll go a bit deeper, but that’s what works for our home at the moment 💗
